This paper presents a technique for generating word embeddings using the structure of Wikipedia, which is a common approach in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) research. The paper also focuses on evaluating the effectiveness of the proposed technique in tasks such as clustering and sorting, which are common in machine learning (ML) and data mining research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and IR research. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning), which cover related topics in ML and AI research.
